&lt;span class=&quot;c1&quot;&gt;#=&amp;gt; prints 'Hi, Tom' to STDOUT.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Check out the &lt;a href=&quot;https://jekyllrb.com/docs/home&quot;&gt;Jekyll docs&lt;/a&gt; for more info on how to get the most out of Jekyll. File all bugs/feature requests at &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/jekyll/jekyll&quot;&gt;Jekyll’s GitHub repo&lt;/a&gt;. If you have questions, you can ask them on &lt;a href=&quot;https://talk.jekyllrb.com/&quot;&gt;Jekyll Talk&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name></name></author><summary type="html">You’ll find this post in your _posts directory. Go ahead and edit it and re-build the site to see your changes. You can rebuild the site in many different ways, but the most common way is to run jekyll serve, which launches a web server and auto-regenerates your site when a file is updated.</summary></entry><entry><title type="html">測試 Docker 開發 ASP.NET</title><link href="http://localhost:4000/docker/2016/05/13/learn-asp-in-docker.html" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="測試 Docker 開發 ASP.NET" /><published>2016-05-13T11:30:00+08:00</published><updated>2016-05-13T11:30:00+08:00</updated><id>http://localhost:4000/docker/2016/05/13/learn-asp-in-docker</id><content type="html" xml:base="http://localhost:4000/docker/2016/05/13/learn-asp-in-docker.html">&lt;p&gt;使用 Docker 開發 ASP.NET，參閱 &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/docker/labs/blob/master/windows/dotnet-core/index.md&quot;&gt;Quickstart .NET Core&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

